Why Work With Us
Benefits

See yourself being part of a large, transformational change? This could be the role for you!


Iress is continuing to hire for roles during Covid-19 with all interviewing and on-boarding done virtually. Everyone new to the team, along with our current staff, will temporarily work from home until it is safe to return to our offices.

Passionate about software engineering and data technologies? Yes, so are we!

Were looking for talented engineers to join us and help us to bring our data products to market. Were aiming to provide greater speed, scale, quality and autonomy to our data engineering teams and we are architecting and delivering this through a combination of poly-cloud architecture, infrastructure automation, DevOps principles, micro-services, API development, SaaS adoption, and use of emerging cloud technologies.

They say variety is the spice of life - well youll be building cloud infrastructure, developing data services and capabilities, and shipping software to our clients and end-users.

Youll also be providing technical advice and expertise to our engineering teams and helping them to focus on innovation, as well as promoting the adoption and re-use of the Iress technology platform. Youll need to be a good talker and someone who is driven by client and user feedback, consistently striving for ways to improve and automate processes.

We are building data products with a variety of technologies and practices and youll be getting your hands' dirty building solutions that use databases, APIs, ETL, streaming, and analytics/ML.

Dedication to applying DevOps concepts (e.g. CI/CD) to improve the software delivery process is important to us too and youll need to be well versed in Cloud technologies (ideally AWS but Azure or GCP is okay with us) and associated infrastructure-as-code technologies (Terraform, CloudFormation, Ansible, Packer).

Were looking for forward-thinking engineers who have a background in software architecture, application development or data engineering at scale (or any of the other good bits in between).

You may currently be working as a Data Architect, Application Developer or DevOps Engineer; as long as you want to take a hands-on role in producing end-user facing products, powered by data technologies, then thats okay with us! Essentially, we are looking for T-shaped engineers who can work as part of a cross-functional team to get insight orientated products into the hands of our clients and end-users.

Sounds like you? Do you want to hear about us?

Iress is a technology company that began as a start-up. Now, around 500,000 people use our software to help them perform better and deliver more. We believe creating an inclusive workplace, where people feel supported to be their best both at work and at home, is how we'll achieve great things. We support flexible working and offer employee benefits designed to support our people at every stage of life - some of the best in the industry.

This is only part of our story. If you want to see more check out Iress on LinkedIn.

Life At Iress
Why Iress?
Community

Our story began in Australia in 1993.

Back then it was just a few of us developing specialised financial markets trading software from a small room. Fast forward a couple of decades and were one of the leading suppliers of innovative technology solutions for clients in the financial markets, wealth management, and mortgage sectors. Our ever-expanding team and offices cover the globe across Australia, Asia, Canada, New Zealand, South Africa and the UK, and we just keep growing.

Global expertise, local relevance

We may be global but we havent lost our focus. In fact we think the benefit of our global expertise combined with our local market knowledge makes for something very special. Its what enables us to provide outstanding financial services software solutions that are tailored to each region and that deliver truly transformational results for our clients.
